The paper deals with the construction of linear codes over finite chain rings, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of selection criteria and greedy algorithms, which are common techniques in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The construction of codes over rings is also relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents examples of codes over $\mathbb{Z}_4$ and $\mathbb{F}_2+u\mathbb{F}_2$, which are topics in algebra and number theory (cs.SI).
